Package org.jboss.windup.rules.apps.java.model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AbstractJavaSourceModel
    This represents Java source code as an abstract concept.
    AmbiguousJavaClassModel  
    AmbiguousReferenceModel<REFERENCETYPE extends WindupVertexFrame>  
    EarArchiveModel  
    HasManifestFilesModel
    Contains links to JarManifestModels.
    IgnoredFilesReportModel
    Report model containing all the information needed for the report listing all the ignored files during the windup process with all the ignore regexes they were matched against.
    JarArchiveModel
    Represents a .jar archive.
    JarManifestModel
    Contains information from the META-INF/MANIFEST.MF file within an archive.
    JavaApplicationOverviewReportModel
    Represents an overview of the Java application.
    JavaClassFileModel
    This Model represents Java class files on disk (eg, /path/to/Foo.class).
    JavaClassModel
    Represents a JavaClass, either from a .class file or a .java source file.
    JavaMethodModel
    Represents a Java Method within a JavaClassModel
    JavaParameterModel
    Contains information regarding parameters to a Java Method.
    JavaSourceFileModel
    Represents a source ".java" file on disk.
    PackageModel
    Contains a Java package name
    PhantomJavaClassModel
    A JavaClassModel that has not yet been found.
    PropertiesModel
    Represents a Java-style Properties file.
    WarArchiveModel  
    WindupJavaConfigurationModel
    Configuration options that are specific to the Java Ruleset
